An Ode in which Nereus is represented as predicting the fall of Troy to Paris when carrying off Helen. Many treat it in connexion with the preced- ing Ode as an allegory‚ Paris being Antony, Helen Cleopatra, while one critic even explains the scansion of line 36 by saying that Iliacas suggests Niliacas. More probably it is merely an attempt to treat epic material m lyric style.
